name: Logain Ablar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Previously a False Dragon; gentled by the White Tower and Healed by Nynaeve al'Meara; later a sworn ally to Rand al'Thor and a leading Asha'man. In A Memory of Light, Logain becomes the new leader of the Black Tower.

name: Jonan Adley
author: Robert Jordan
description: Early recruit of the Black Tower. Killed when Rand al'Thor lost control of Callandor in Altara.

name: .mw-parser-output .vanchor>
author: Robert Jordan
description: target~.vanchor-text{background-color

name: Lelaine Akashi
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai, Sitter, and First Selector of the Blue Ajah.

name: Nalesean Aldiaya
author: Robert Jordan
description: Deceased commander of the Band of the Red Hand.

name: Algarin Pendaloan
author: Robert Jordan
description: Tairen Lord with potential to be an Asha'man. Part of Logain's faction in the Black Tower, under the name "Emarin".

name: Alivia
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Seanchan damane. Most powerful female channeler alive.

name: Katerine Alruddin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Red Ajah. Killed in Tel'aran'rhiod by Egwene al'Vere.

name: Doesine Alwain
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah. She was part of the group of Aes Sedai using the Oath Rod to reveal sisters of the Black Ajah in the White Tower. She was killed in the Last Battle.

name: Guaire Amalasan
author: Robert Jordan
description: A previous False Dragon who conquered nearly half of the Westlands in the War of the Second Dragon. Defeated by Artur Hawkwing, and gentled by the White Tower.

name: Amathera
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Panarch of Tarabon. Love interest of Juilin Sandar.

name: Merana Ambrey
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Grey Ajah.

name: Amys
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel Wise One. One of Aviendha's and Egwene's primary mentors.

name: Anaiya
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Blue Ajah. Killed by Aran'gar.

name: Setalle Anan
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Aes Sedai of the Brown Ajah who was burned out and becomes an innkeeper in Ebou Dar.

name: Sashalle Anderly
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Red Ajah stilled by Rand and Healed by Damer Flinn.

name: Rianna Andomeran
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the White Ajah. Held prisoner in a stedding.

name: Anlee
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and former Sitter of the Blue Ajah.

name: Naean Arawn
author: Robert Jordan
description: Andoran noblewoman. Attempts to claim the Lion Throne following Morgase's disappearance, but is arrested and imprisoned by Dyelin. Later freed by Arymilla and forced to support her claim to the throne. Taken prisoner by Elayne after Arymilla's attack on Caemlyn is foiled, and stripped of all lands and titles. Later offered new lands in Cairhien by Elayne.

name: Asmodean
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Joar Addam Nessosin. In The Shadow Rising, Lanfear, another Forsaken, forces Asmodean to become Rand al'Thor's mentor. Balefired by Graendal.

name: Saerin Asnobar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter of the Brown Ajah. She was part of the group of Aes Sedai using the Oath Rod to reveal sisters of the Black Ajah in the White Tower.

name: Rhadam Asunawa
author: Robert Jordan
description: High Inquisitor, leader of the Hand of the Light (an organisation within the Children of the Light). His fanaticism ultimately proved too much even for the other Children, and he was executed to make way for Galad to become Lord Captain Commander.

name: Aviendha
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel. Maiden of the Spear, later a Wise One, and one of Rand al'Thor's paramours.

name: Perrin Aybara
author: Robert Jordan
description: ta'veren; Central character of the series; former blacksmith and woodworker; capable of telepathic communication with wolves, as well as being able to visit Tel'aran'rhiod. Named 'Young Bull' by the wolves and 'Lord Goldeneyes' by his followers. Husband of Faile Bashere. (Side Note

name: Edesina Azzedin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Yellow Ajah and former damane.

name: Bain
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel Maiden of the Spear. First-Sister to Chiad.

name: Bair
author: Robert Jordan
description: Wise One of the Haido sept of the Shaarad Ariel. Cannot channel, but is an experienced dreamwalker.

name: Balthamel
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Eval Ramman. Killed at the Eye of the World by the Green Man. Later reincarnated by the Dark One as Aran'gar, in a female body. Is balefired when Rand destroys Graendal's lair.

name: Balwer
author: Robert Jordan
description: Secretary and spymaster to Perrin Aybara, former spymaster for Pedron Niall of the Children of the Light.

name: Teslyn Baradon
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Red Ajah. Briefly damane.

name: Narenwin Barda
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah.

name: Duhara Basaheen
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Red Ajah. Killed by Aviendha.

name: Davram Bashere
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the five 'Great Captains'. Born in Saldaea. Commanded the Army of the Light in Caemlyn in the Last Battle, where he died.

name: Zarine (Faile) Bashere
author: Robert Jordan
description: Daughter of Davram Bashere. Wife of Perrin Aybara. Cousin to the queen of Saldaea.

name: Adelorna Bastine
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Captain-General of the Green Ajah.

name: Sheriam Bayanar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Blue Ajah. Once the Mistress of Novices, then Egwene's Keeper of the Chronicles until discovered and purged.

name: Be'lal
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Duram Laddel Cham. Infiltrated Tear under the alias of Lord Samon. Balefired by Moiraine Damodred during the battle for the Stone of Tear.

name: Myrelle Berengari
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah and Captain-General for the rebels.

name: Falion Bhoda
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the White Ajah. Killed by Aviendha.

name: Nesune Bihara
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Brown Ajah.

name: Jesse Bilal
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and First Chair of the Brown Ajah.

name: Erian Boroleos
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Green Ajah.

name: Silviana Brehon
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Red Ajah. Former Mistress of Novices and Keeper of the Chronicles to Egwene.

name: Gareth Bryne
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the five 'Great Captains'. Originally from Andor. Suspected paramour of Queen Morgase. Warder to Siuan Sanche. Commanded the Army of the Light in Kandor in the Last Battle, in which he died.

name: Joiya Byir
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Grey Ajah. Killed by Slayer.

name: Jeaine Caide
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Green Ajah. Killed by Thom.

name: Gaidal Cain
author: Robert Jordan
description: A Hero of the Horn, known as the lover and companion of Birgitte.

name: Adine Canford
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah.

name: Canler
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man in the Black Tower loyal to Logain Ablar.

name: Carlinya Sorevin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the White Ajah. Killed during the fight in Tel'aran'rhiod against Mesaana

name: Carlomin
author: Robert Jordan
description: A Tairen Lord. Banner-General in the Band of the Red Hand, he leads a banner of cavalry in Altara.

name: Galina Casban
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister and former Highest of the Red Ajah. Now gai'shain of the Shaido.

name: Romanda Cassin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah. Sitter and First Weaver in the Tower. Died in the Last Battle.

name: Matrim (Mat) Cauthon
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the main characters. Ta'veren and childhood companion of Perrin Aybara and Rand al'Thor; Captain-General of the Band of the Red Hand; later consort of Tuon/Fortuona, with the title 'Prince of the Ravens'. Mat is known to the Aelfinn and Eelfinn as 'Son of Battles' and to the Heroes of the Horn as 'The Gambler'. Former Hornblower of the Horn of Valere.

name: Merilille Ceandevin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Grey Ajah.

name: Noal Charin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Member of the Band of the Red Hand, also known as legendary traveler 'Jain Farstrider'. Hero of the Horn.

name: Chiad
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel Maiden of the Spear. First-sister to Bain, love interest of Gaul.

name: Rafela Cindal
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah.

name: Couladin
author: Robert Jordan
description: The leader of the Shaido Aiel and false Car'a'carn. Killed by Mat Cauthon.

name: Theodrin Dabei
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Brown Ajah.

name: Zerah Dacan
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the White Ajah.

name: Nisao Dachen
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah. Her Warder is Sarin Hoigan.

name: Mistress Daelvin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Innkeeper of the Golden Stag in Maerone. (VI-138)

name: Masema Dagar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Shienaran soldier. Considers himself Prophet of the Dragon. Killed by Faile.

name: Caraline Damodred
author: Robert Jordan
description: Cousin of Moiraine Damodred, formerly rebel against Rand al'Thor. Wife of Darlin Sisnera

name: Galadedrid (Galad) Damodred
author: Robert Jordan
description: Half-brother of Elayne and Gawyn Trakand on his father's side, and as son of Tigraine Mantear, also Rand al'Thor's half-brother. Eventually Lord Captain Commander of the Children of the Light.

name: Moiraine Damodred
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah. Mentor to the protagonists in the first three books; supporting-character afterward.

name: Dark One
author: Robert Jordan
description: the supreme antagonist of the series; known by a variety of nicknames ('Old Grim'; 'Father of Lies'; 'Heart of the Dark'; etc.) to evade drawing his attention by repetition of his true name ('Shai'tan'

name: Raolin Darksbane
author: Robert Jordan
description: A previous False Dragon, gentled by the White Tower.

name: Corlan Dashiva
author: Robert Jordan
description: Guise of Aginor while in the Black Tower.

name: Cetalia Delarme
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah. Former head of the eyes-and-ears for the Blue. Killed by the Black Ajah.

name: Talmanes Delovinde
author: Robert Jordan
description: A Lord of Cairhien. He leads the Altara contingent of three banners supplemented by a large group of crossbowmen. Right-hand man of Mat in the Band of the Red Hand.

name: Demandred
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Barid Bel Medar. Leader of the Sharans. Killed by Lan Mandragoran in the Field of Merrilor.

name: Bayle Domon
author: Robert Jordan
description: Recurring character; Captain of the ferryboat Spray. Taken as da'covale by the Seanchan and made so'jhin by Egeanin Sarna. Later released and wedded by Egeanin.

name: Norine Dovarna
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the White Ajah.

name: Eadyth
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and former Sitter and First Selector of the Blue Ajah.

name: Edorion
author: Robert Jordan
description: A Tairen Lord. Banner-General in the Band of the Red Hand, he leads a banner of horse in Altara under Talmanes.

name: Elswell
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of unknown Ajah.

name: Chesmal Emry
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah formerly of the Yellow Ajah. Killed by Elayne Trakand.

name: Enkazin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man. Friend of Saml al'Seen from the Two Rivers.

name: Demira Eriff
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Brown Ajah.  She has one Warder, Stevan.

name: Erith
author: Robert Jordan
description: Ogier, wife of Loial.

name: Estean
author: Robert Jordan
description: Lieutenant-General in the Band of the Red Hand, he commands the cavalry of the Murandy contingent, particularly three banners of horse.

name: Padan Fain
author: Robert Jordan
description: traveling merchant, spying for the Dark One, who later becomes fused with Mashadar. A recurring villain. Killed by Mat. Known for carrying a dagger from Shadar Logoth, which kills anyone who touches its blade.

name: Elmindreda (Min) Farshaw
author: Robert Jordan
description: Clairvoyante; one of Rand al'Thor's three principal paramours. Sees visions or auras around people's heads, which are always true.

name: Tarna Feir
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Red Ajah. Turned to the Shadow.

name: Dagdara Finchey
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Yellow Ajah.

name: Damer Flinn
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the oldest Asha'man, the first to be tested for the ability. Bonded as a Warder to Corele Hovian. Best male Talent at healing, on par with Nynaeve.

name: Andaya Forae
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter of the Grey Ajah.

name: Careane Fransi
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Green Ajah. Killed by Vandene Namelle.

name: Alviarin Freidhen
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the White Ajah. Head of the Black Ajah Supreme Council. Keeper to Elaida. Held prisoner in a stedding.

name: Ryma Galfrey
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah. Now a damane named Pura.

name: Gaul
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel Stone Dog. Companion of Perrin Aybara.

name: Toveine Gazal
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and former Sitter of the Red Ajah. Bonded by Logain and Turned to the Shadow.

name: Charl Gedwyn
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man that was part of the plot to kill Rand al'Thor in Cairhien. Killed by Padan Fain/Mordeth.

name: Marillin Gemalphin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Brown Ajah.

name: Androl Genhald
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man in the Black Tower loyal to Logain Ablar. Extremely weak in the Power but with the Talent of making Gateways. Mutually bonded to Pevara Tazanovni.

name: Jur Grady
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the original Asha'man recruits. Accompanies Perrin Aybara.

name: Graendal
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken, a master of Compulsion. Originally named Kamarile Maradim Nindar. Killed by Shaidar Haran and resurrected by the Dark One as Hessalam. Hit by the backfiring of her own Compulsion weave during the Last Battle.

name: Merise Haindehl
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah. Bonded the Asha'man Jahar Narishma as Warder.

name: Shaidar Haran
author: Robert Jordan
description: Myrddraal. A principal agent of the Dark One.

name: Faeldrin Harella
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah. Killed in the Last Battle.

name: Bera Harkin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah.

name: Harldin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Harldin is one of the Asha'man in the Black Tower loyal to Logain Ablar.

name: Artur Hawkwing
author: Robert Jordan
description: Full name Artur Paendrag Tanreall, general and emperor who conquered most of the story's world a thousand years before the Last Battle; similar to Genghis Khan and implied to be the source of the legends of King Arthur.

name: Seaine Herimon
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter of the White Ajah. She was part of the group of Aes Sedai using the Oath Rod to reveal sisters of the Black Ajah in the White Tower.

name: Eben Hopwil
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man bonded by Daigian Moseneillin. Killed by Aran'gar as he attempts to shield his Aes Sedai from the Forsaken's attack.

name: Corele Hovian
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah. She bonded Asha'man Damer Flinn.

name: Hurin
author: Robert Jordan
description: A 'thief-taker' in service of the King of Shienar. Has the gift of "smelling" violence. Accompanied Rand al'Thor in the world of the Portal Stones. Killed in the Last Battle.

name: Hopper
author: Robert Jordan
description: Perrin Aybara's deceased wolf friend and mentor.

name: Ishamael
author: Robert Jordan
description: The most powerful member of the Forsaken; originally named Elan Morin Tedronai. Known as the "Betrayer of Hope". Caused Lews Therin Telamon to commit suicide. Resurrected as Moridin after being killed by Rand al'Thor. Chosen as Nae'blis by the Dark One. The only other man who was equal in power to Lews Therin Telamon and Rand al'Thor

name: Rodel Ituralde
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the five 'Great Captains'. Fought the Seanchan in Arad Doman until being brought to the Saldaean front by the Dragon Reborn. Commanded the Army of the Light in Shayol Ghul during the Last Battle. Almost certainly Arad Doman's new monarch after the Last Battle.

name: Agelmar Jagad
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the five 'Great Captains', Shienaran, leads the Borderlander Army of the Light at Tarwin's Gap during the Last Battle.

name: Eldrith Jhondar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Brown Ajah. Killed by Doilin Mellar/Daved Hanlon.

name: Janduin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Clan Chief of the Tardaad Aiel and biological father of Rand al'Thor. Killed by Slayer in the Blight.

name: Welyn Kajima
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man.

name: Furyk Karede
author: Robert Jordan
description: Seanchan Banner-General of the Deathwatch Guard, he led the search for the High Lady Tuon.[2]

name: Moria Karentanis
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter of the Blue Ajah. Also Black Ajah. Purged.

name: Alliandre Maritha Kigarin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Queen of Ghealdan.

name: Temaile Kinderode
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Gray Ajah. Killed by Doilin Mellar/Daved Hanlon.

name: Tylee Kirgan
author: Robert Jordan
description: A general in the Seanchan army.

name: Raefar Kisman
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man that was part of the plot to kill Rand al'Thor in Cairhien.

name: Kumira Dhoran
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Brown Ajah. Killed by Graendal in the Battle near Shadar Logoth.

name: Mezar Kurin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man in the Black Tower loyal to Logain Ablar.

name: Lanfear
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally known as Mierin Eronaile; sometime paramour to Lews Therin Telamon. Most powerful of the female Forsaken. Killed by Moridin in the realm of the Aelfinn, returned as Cyndane and killed by Perrin at the Last Battle.

name: Annoura Larisen
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Grey Ajah, advisor and companion to Berelain, First of Mayene. Burned out rescuing Galad from his battle with Demandred.

name: Atuan Larisett
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Yellow Ajah.

name: Leane Sharif
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Keeper of the Chronicles under Siuan Sanche. Stilled, but Healed by Nyneave.

name: Liandrin Guirale
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Red Ajah. Now a damane.

name: Loial
author: Robert Jordan
description: Ogier. Close friend to Perrin Aybara and Rand al'Thor.

name: Lyrelle Arienwin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter of the Blue Ajah.

name: Machin Shin
author: Robert Jordan
description: 'Black Wind'; a malevolent intelligent force occupying the Ogier's 'Ways'.  Steals the souls of those who touch it.

name: Elyas Machera
author: Robert Jordan
description: Wolfbrother, husband and former Warder to Rina Hafden. Friend to Perrin.

name: Maigan
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah.

name: Arel Malevin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man.

name: Mandevwin
author: Robert Jordan
description: A Cairhienen. Banner-General in the Band of the Red Hand, he commands the crossbowmen temporarily attached to the Altaran cavalry contingent.

name: al'Lan (Lan) Mandragoran
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Warder to Moiraine Damodred, currently Warder and husband to Nynaeve al'Meara. King of Malkier, which was lost to the Shadow when he was a child. Greatest swordsman of the Third Age, defeated Demandred in single combat by "sheathing the sword".

name: Karldin Manfor
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man. Bonded as Warder by Beldeine Nyram of Green Ajah. Killed by Sharans in the Last Battle.

name: Tigraine Mantear
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Queen of Andor, mother of Galad Damodred and later of Rand al'Thor. Died giving birth on the slopes of Dragonmount.

name: Beonin Marinye
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Grey Ajah.

name: Arymilla Marne
author: Robert Jordan
description: Andoran noblewoman. Put forward a claim to the Lion Throne following Morgase's disappearance. Attempted to conquer Caemlyn from Elayne, but was defeated and stripped of all lands and titles. Later offered new lands in Cairhien by Elayne.

name: Mashadar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Malevolent intelligence inhabiting the city of Aridhol, alias 'Shadar Logoth'. Takes the form of a killing mist. Inhabited the body of Padan Fain, who was later killed by Matrim Cauthon.

name: Verin Mathwin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Brown Ajah. Spy for the Light.

name: Joline Maza
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Green Ajah.

name: Nynaeve al'Meara
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the main protagonists. Wisdom of Emond's Field and eventual Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah. Wife to Lan and thus Queen of Malkier. Discovered methods for healing both Stilling/Gentling and madness.

name: Cabriana Mecandes
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah. Tortured and killed by Semirhage.

name: Meidani Eschede
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Grey Ajah.

name: Cadsuane Melaidhrin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Legendary Aes Sedai of the Green Ajah. Amyrlin Seat after the Last Battle.

name: Thom Merrilin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Gleeman and adventurer; former bard to Queen Morgase; also her paramour. Married and Warder to Moiraine Damodred.

name: Mesaana
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Saine Tarasind. Incapacitated, her mind snapped in Tel'aran'rhiod by Egwene al'Vere.

name: Talene Minly
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Green Ajah.

name: Atal Mishraile
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man loyal to Mazrim Taim.

name: Beslan Mitsobar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Heir to the throne of Altara, and later King. Friend to Mat Cauthon.

name: Tylin Quintara Mitsobar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Queen of Altara. Mother to Beslan. Kept Mat Cauthon as her paramour. Killed by a gholam.

name: Miyasi
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the White Ajah.

name: Ilyena Moerelle
author: Robert Jordan
description: Wife of Lews Therin Telamon and slain by him.

name: Moghedien
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Lilen Moiral. Nicknamed webspinner. Now a damane.

name: Luthair Paendrag Mondwin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Son of Artur Hawkwing, who sailed across the Aryth Ocean and claimed the lands of Seanchan for his father's empire.

name: Mordeth
author: Robert Jordan
description: Councilor in the city of Aridhol; now a phantom destroying all intruders.

name: Gitara Moroso
author: Robert Jordan
description: Advisor to Mordrellen Mantear and Keeper of the Chronicles to Tamra Ospenya. Died Foretelling the rebirth of the Dragon.

name: Fedwin Morr
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the first Asha'man. Killed by Rand al'Thor as a mercy once Morr falls victim to the taint on saidin.

name: Morvrin Thakanos
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Brown Ajah.

name: Delana Mosalaine
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Grey Ajah. Balefired by Rand in the assault on Graendal's lair.

name: Daigian Moseneillin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the White Ajah. Killed by Shaidar Haran.

name: Alanna Mosvani
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah. Bonded to Rand. Killed by Moridin in the Last Battle.

name: Kiruna Nachiman
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah. Killed in the Last Battle.

name: Malind Nachenin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and former Sitter of the Green Ajah.

name: Amico Nagoyin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Yellow Ajah. Killed by Slayer.

name: Aeldra Najaf
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah and Keeper of the Chronicles for Tamra Ospenya.

name: Arlen Nalaam
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man.

name: Adeleas Namelle
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Brown Ajah. Sister to Vandene Namelle. Killed by Careane Fransi.

name: Vandene Namelle
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah. Sister to Adeleas Namelle. Killed by Chesmal Emry.

name: Jahar Narishma
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man loyal to Rand al'Thor. Bonded as Warder by Merise Haindehl.

name: Berylla Naron
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Blue Ajah.

name: Fager Neald
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man of soldier rank. Accompanies Perrin Aybara in his mission to find Masema.

name: Ferane Neheran
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai, Sitter, and First Reasoner the White Ajah.

name: Sarene Nemdahl
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the White Ajah. She is more than beautiful and her warder's name is Vitalien. Compelled and used up by Hessalam during the Last Battle.

name: Aludra Nendenhald
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aludra is an Illuminator originally from Tarabon. She created the Dragons and Dragon Eggs (Cannons and exploding cannonballs) with help from Mat Cauthon and Elayne Trakand.

name: Varil Nensen
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man.

name: Pedron Niall
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Lord Captain Commander of the Children of the Light. One of the five 'Great Captains'.

name: Norley
author: Robert Jordan
description: Norley is one of the Asha'man in the Black Tower loyal to Logain Ablar.

name: Beldeine Nyram
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai sister of the Green Ajah. Killed by Sharans in the Last Battle.

name: Ogier
author: Robert Jordan
description: a species of anthropoid; hirsute, wide-featured, and immense in height and strength; intelligent, long-lived, and typically peaceful. Proficient in wood-carving and masonry; given to inventing long, elaborate names; immersed in historical and genealogical study; sedentary as a rule. Typically confined to the sanctuaries known as 'stedding' (a variation probably of 'Steading'), in which the One Power is inaccessible. When roused, they are a fearsome force in battle.

name: Olver
author: Robert Jordan
description: Orphan and companion/adoptee to the Band of the Red Hand. Becomes Hornblower of the Horn of Valere.

name: Daerid Ondin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Lieutenant-General in the Band of the Red Hand, he commands five banners of foot soldiers in the Murandy group.

name: Faolain Orande
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah.

name: Tamra Ospenya
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Amyrlin Seat raised from the Blue Ajah. Tortured and killed by the Black Ajah.

name: Birlen Pena
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister.

name: Elza Penfell
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Green Ajah. Balefired by Rand.

name: Rand al'Thor
author: Robert Jordan
description: Main protagonist of the story. The Dragon Reborn, known as the Car'a'carn or He Who Comes with the Dawn to the Aiel, known as the Coramoor to the Atha'an Miere, and known as Shadowkiller to the wolves. Born on the slopes of Dragonmount during the Aiel War. The reincarnated soul of Lews Therin Telamon.

name: Rahvin
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Ared Mosinel. Used Compulsion on Queen Morgase of Andor in order to take control of the country, under the alias of Lord Gaebril. Was killed with Balefire by Rand.

name: Tsutama Rath
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and former Sitter for the Red Ajah. Current Highest.

name: Merean Redhill
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Blue Ajah. Mistress of Novices under Tamra Ospenya. Killed in Kandor by Moiraine Damodred.

name: Reimon
author: Robert Jordan
description: A Tairen Lord. Banner-General in the Band of the Red Hand, he leads a banner of horse also in Altara.

name: Rhuarc
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel clan chief, husband to Amys and her first-sister. One of Rand's primary allies among the Aiel, and in general. Fell under Hessalam's Compulsion. Killed by Aviendha in the Last Battle.

name: Manel Rochaid
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man that was part of the plot to kill Rand al'Thor in Cairhien. Killed by Rand.

name: Elaida Do Avriny a'Roihan
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Red Ajah. Former advisor to Queen Morgase Trakand and former Amyrlin Seat, having unseated Siuan Sanche. Sent Aes Sedai to kidnap the Dragon Reborn, a mission which resulted in several sisters being captured and forced to swear oaths of fealty to Rand al'Thor. Unwilling pawn to Black Ajah leader Alviarin most of her rule. Taken damane in a Seanchan raid against the White Tower.

name: Robb Solter
author: Robert Jordan
description: Soldier in Perrin's army.

name: Colavaere Saighan
author: Robert Jordan
description: Cairhienin noblewoman. Conspired with Elaida's Aes Sedai to have Rand captured and transported to the White Tower so she could become Queen of Cairhien. Removed from power and stripped of all titles by Rand once he returned to the Sun Palace after being rescued. Committed suicide by hanging.

name: Sammael
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Tel Janin Aellinsar. Took control of Illian, under the alias of Lord Brend. Killed by Mashadar in battle with Rand.

name: Donalo Sandomere
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man in the Black Tower loyal to Logain Ablar.

name: Karale Sanghir
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Grey Ajah.

name: Siuan Sanche
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah. Former head of the eyes-and-ears network for the Blue. Former Amyrlin Seat. Deposed and stilled. Healed by Nynaeve. Becomes Egwene's advisor and mentor as Amyrlin. Bonded Gareth Bryne. Died in the Last Battle.

name: Juilin Sandar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Thief-catcher of Tear.

name: Elenia Sarand
author: Robert Jordan
description: Andoran noblewoman. Attempts to claim the Lion Throne following Morgase's disappearance, but is arrested and imprisoned by Dyelin. Later freed by Arymilla and forced to support her claim to the throne. Taken prisoner by Elayne after Arymilla's attack on Caemlyn is foiled, and stripped of all lands and titles. Later offered new lands in Cairhien by Elayne.

name: Saml al'Seen
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man native to Emond's Field.

name: Selucia
author: Robert Jordan
description: Shadow and Voice to Empress of Seanchan. Briefly Tuon's/Fortuona's Truthspeaker.

name: Semirhage
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the Forsaken; originally named Nemene Damendar Boann. Known for being exceedingly cruel and creative with torture. Masqueraded as Seanchean nobility under the alias of Anath Dorje, becoming the Truthspeaker to the Daughter of the Nine Moons. Destroyed Rand al'Thor's left hand before being captured by him. Released by Elza Penfell at which point she compelled Rand al'Thor with the Domination Band to nearly kill Elmindreda Farshaw. Balefired by Rand, who was utilizing the True Power.

name: Leane Sharif
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah and now of the Green Ajah. Keeper of the Chronicles under Siuan Sanche. Deposed and stilled. Healed by Nynaeve.

name: Ispan Shefar
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Blue Ajah. Killed by Careane Fransi.

name: Ingtar Shinowa
author: Robert Jordan
description: Shienaran nobleman and soldier. Accompanies Rand on the hunt to reclaim the Horn of Valere, after it is stolen by Padan Fain in Fal Dara. Killed by the Seanchan in Falme.

name: Birgitte Silverbow
author: Robert Jordan
description: Hero of the Horn. Warder to Elayne Trakand. Killed in the Last Battle.

name: Betse Silvin
author: Robert Jordan
description: F. Serving-maid in the Golden Stag. Mat dances with her VI-144.

name: Slayer
author: Robert Jordan
description: Being born from the merged souls of Isam Mandragoran, cousin of Lan Mandragoran, and Luc Mantear, maternal uncle of Rand Al'Thor. Hunter for the Shadow, master of Tel'aran'rhiod, enjoys killing wolves. Killed by Perrin Aybara after lengthy rivalry.

name: Masuri Sokawa
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Brown Ajah. She has one Warder, Rovair Kirklin.

name: Someshta
author: Robert Jordan
description: Green Man, last of the Nym. Guardian of the Eye of the World. Died killing the Forsaken Balthamel.

name: Sorilea
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel Wise One. Very weak in the Power, but arguably the most influential of all the Wise Ones.

name: Fera Sormen
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the White Ajah.

name: Kairen Stang
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah. Killed by Aran'gar.

name: Mattin Stepaneos den Balgar
author: Robert Jordan
description: King of Illian. Kidnapped by the White Tower under Elaida.

name: Yurian Stonebow
author: Robert Jordan
description: A previous False Dragon who could channel.

name: Aeldene Stonebridge
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Blue Ajah.

name: Sulin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aiel Maiden of the Spear, companion of both Rand and Perrin.

name: Dobraine Taborwin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Cairhienin nobleman. Assists in the rescue of Rand from Elaida's Aes Sedai at Dumai's Wells. Later appointed steward of Cairhien by Rand.

name: Mazrim Taim
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man, False Dragon, and new Forsaken. M'Hael of the Black Tower. He used his position to secretly Turn Asha'man to the Shadow. Killed by Egwene al'Vere in the Last Battle.

name: Takima Deraighdin
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter for the Brown Ajah.

name: Samitsu Tamagowa
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Yellow Ajah. Her warder is named Roshan.

name: Berelain sur Paendrag Paeron
author: Robert Jordan
description: First (leading statesman) of Mayene. Romantically pursues Perrin Aybara aggressively until reaching an accommodation with his wife. Otherwise a cunning and intelligent politician and loyal ally to Perrin.

name: Pevara Tazanovni
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter for the Red Ajah. Bonded to and Bonded by Androl Genhald. She was part of the group of Aes Sedai using the Oath Rod to reveal sisters of the Black Ajah in the White Tower.

name: Lews Therin Telamon
author: Robert Jordan
description: Dragon, Lord of Morning, Kinslayer, led the Hundred Companions in the fight against the Shadow in the War of Power before beginning the Breaking of the World.

name: Therava
author: Robert Jordan
description: Shaido Aiel Wise One and master of former Black Ajah Aes Sedai Galina Casban.

name: Rand al'Thor
author: Robert Jordan
description: Protagonist; reincarnation of Lews Therin Telamon, and heir to his role. He is The Dragon Reborn and is known as The Car'a'carn by the Aiel, the Coramoor by the Atha'an miere and as Shadowkiller by the wolf brothers.  Fated to battle the Dark One in every life.

name: Tam al'Thor
author: Robert Jordan
description: Adoptive father of Rand al'Thor. Blademaster.

name: Marris Thornhill
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Brown Ajah.

name: Salita Toranes
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and former Sitter for the Yellow Ajah.

name: Peral Torval
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man part of the plot to kill Rand al'Thor in Cairhien. Killed by Padan Fain.

name: Seonid Traighan
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai of the Green Ajah.

name: Elayne Trakand
author: Robert Jordan
description: One of the main protagonists. Heir to the throne of Andor, and later Queen. Aes Sedai of the Green Ajah. Paramour of Rand al'Thor. Has the Talent of making ter'angreal.

name: Gawyn Trakand
author: Robert Jordan
description: Brother of Elayne and half-brother to Galad Damodred. Leader of the Younglings. Warder to Egwene al'Vere. Died fighting Demandred during the Last Battle.

name: Morgase Trakand
author: Robert Jordan
description: Queen of Andor. Mother of Gawyn and Elayne.

name: Nicola Treehill
author: Robert Jordan
description: Novice in training with the sisters in Salidar. Killed in Tel'aran'rhiod. Has the Talent of Foretelling.

name: Tuon/Fortuona
author: Robert Jordan
description: Seanchan royal, called 'Daughter of the Nine Moons'; later Empress. Leader of the Seanchan invasion force. Wife of Mat Cauthon. The name is a play on 'Fortune', among other references, in her relationship with Mat, to Probability. Also a Sul'dam.

name: Eamon Valda
author: Robert Jordan
description: Former Lord Captain Commander of the Children of the Light. Blademaster. Killed by Galad Damodred.

name: Egwene al'Vere
author: Robert Jordan
description: Main character in the series. Initially the lover of Rand al'Thor. Had the Talent of Dreamwalking. Discovered the counter-weave for Balefire. Former Amyrlin Seat. Bonded her love interest Gawyn Trakand until his death, then briefly Egeanin/Leilwin until shortly before her death in the Last Battle.

name: Evin Vinchova
author: Robert Jordan
description: Asha'man in the Black Tower, Turned to the Shadow by Mazrim Taim. Tricked into (suicide) attacking his compatriots by Androl.

name: Yoeli
author: Robert Jordan
description: An officer in the Saldaean army.

name: Yukiri Haruna
author: Robert Jordan
description: Aes Sedai and Sitter for the Grey Ajah. She was part of the group of Aes Sedai using the Oath Rod to reveal sisters of the Black Ajah in the White Tower.

name: Asne Zeramene
author: Robert Jordan
description: Black Ajah sister formerly of the Green Ajah. Killed by Sea Folk Windfinders.
